  "learn": {
    "heading": "Three ways, one amount",
    "intro": "<p><strong>Percent</strong> means \"out of 100.\" So a percent is just a fraction with 100 on the bottom, which is also an easy decimal.</p>",
    "examples": [
      "<strong>50% = 50/100 = 0.5 = 1/2</strong> — all the same half.",
      "<strong>25% = 25/100 = 0.25 = 1/4</strong>. To go from percent to decimal, slide the dot 2 places: 25% → 0.25."
    ]
  },
